From 5ad01c96fb1a68703575cc3613f5cc1794b67356 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nagarajan Maran <nmaran@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 25 Aug 2025 11:28:29 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: CP: wifi: ath12k: Rewrite bridge vdev removal
 logic

Refactor bridge vdev handling to align with the latest upstream design.

Previously, AP vdev stop, self peer delete, and vdev delete were handled via a
single mac80211 ops callback (ath12k_mac_op_unassign_vif_chanctx). The updated upstream
design separates these operations: vdev stop remains in
"ath12k_mac_op_unassign_vif_chanctx", while self peer delete and vdev delete are
moved to "ath12k_mac_op_change_vif_links".

Update bridge vdev logic to follow the same flow as normal vdevs, ensuring operations are
performed only after all normal vdevs in that MLD complete their respective transitions.

Changes include:
	1) Trigger bridge vdev down for AP/WDS AP MLD only after confirming all normal
	   vdevs are down, replacing the previous links_map check.
	2) Trigger bridge vdev stop for AP/WDS AP MLD only after confirming all normal
	   vdevs have stopped, replacing the previous links_map check.
	3) Handle self peer delete and vdev down for AP/WDS AP MLD and STA/WDS STA MLD
	   via "ath12k_mac_op_change_vif_links" callback, ensuring bridge vdev cleanup
	   occurs only after normal vdevs are removed. With the latest upstream design it
	   was being handled as part of "ath12k_mac_op_remove_interface"

Also, improve logging for better debuggability.

Fixes: 6812a0129cf8 ("CP: wifi: ath12k: UD rework for NLINK MLO feature")
Patch-dependency:
	0327-02-wifi-ath12k-n-link-mlo-bridge-vdev-create-start.patch
	0327-03-wifi-ath12k-n-link-mlo-bridge-vdev-up-and-channel-switch.patch
Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Nagarajan Maran <nmaran@qti.qualcomm.com>
